programme.title: Gorgo
programme.desc: Greedy sailors tangle with and capture Gorgo, a giant lizard, off the coast of Ireland and sell him to a London circus. Gorgo's mother, mad with rage, follows his trail to London leaving a wake of destruction in her path.

programme.title: White Zombie (1932)
programme.desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. They’re soon wishing they’d gone to Cancun! This Pre-­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The film’s unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DON’T LOOK INTO LUGOSI’S EYES!

programme.title: The Sadist
programme.desc: Written and directed by James Landis, this thriller loosely follows the story of the killing spree of Charles Starkweather (later films Badlands, 1973, and Natural Born Killers, 1994, were also based on Starkweather’s tale). Starring Arch Hall, Jr. The Sadist begins with three high school teachers driving through California. Unfortunately, their car breaks down in an abandoned area, where they experience a run in with a bloodthirsty sadist and his girlfriend. A truly terrifying experience, this film will have you on the edge of your seat from start to finish!

programme.title: Scared To Death
programme.desc: The only color film to star Bela Lugosi was this mystery thriller from director Christy Cabanne (The Mummy’s Hand) made for the short­lived Golden Gate Pictures during the early months of 1946. Lugosi plays Professor Leonide, a cagy character who may have had something to do with the death of a young woman (who happens to be telling her tale from a slab at the morgue!). George Zucco, Molly Lamont, and Joyce Compton also star, as well as Angelo Rossitto, (Freaks) as a menacing dwarf with a habit of stepping on Lugosi’s foot!

programme.title: She Gods of Shark Reef
programme.desc: Two brothers, including one wanted for murder, are shipwrecked on an island inhabited by beautiful woman who possess a cache of valuable pearls. What the brothers don't know is that the island women worship a shark god, and are known to make human sacrifices! With a cast that includes the smoldering Lisa Montell, this intense adventure was directed by drive-in movie king Roger Corman. For movie buffs: Corman made the most of location shooting, filming Shark Reef in the same Hawaiian setting as Naked Paradise (1957).

programme.title: Mesa of Lost Women
programme.desc: Spider-women lure men to their death in this thriller from the golden era of Drive-in schlock! This story of a mad scientist (Jackie Coogan) is regarded as one of the worst movies ever made. Still, dig the crazy guitar and piano score which was purloined by Ed Wood Jr. for Jail Bait, and notice a couple of Wood regulars (Dolores Fuller and Lyle Talbot) in the credits. What you have here is a sort of cousin to the films of Ed Wood, but one that can stand on its own as being truly awful. Enjoy!

programme.title: The Brain That Wouldn't Die (1962)
programme.desc: While driving to his family’s country house, Dr. Bill Cortner (Jason Evers) and his fiancée, Jan Compton (Virginia Leith) get into a horrible car accident, leaving Jan decapitated. An expert in transplants, Dr. Cortner rushes to his lab with Jan’s severed head, and searches for a way to save his fiancée. Keeping her head alive in a liquid-filled tray, Dr. Cortner searches for a woman to murder in the hope that he may transplant Jan’s head onto a new body. His efforts lead to chaotic results. Written and directed by Joseph Green, this 1962 flick will be sure to keep you at the edge of your seat from beginning to end!

programme.title: House On Haunted Hill
programme.desc: A millionaire offers ten thousand dollars to five people if they agree to stay overnight in a large, spooky, rented house. When you consider that the millionaire is Vincent Price, and the film is directed by schlock master William Castle, you can bet the five guests are in for a long, bumpy night. This "super shocker of the century" was a smash hit upon its 1959 release. For architecture buffs, the home used for the exteriors of the haunted house was actually designed by Frank Lloyd Wright and built in 1924!

programme.title: Carnival of Souls (1962)
programme.desc: "Carnival of Souls" is the story of a young woman who goes along for the ride when two hot-rodders hold a drag race and are forced off a bridge, plunging into the flooded river below. The sole survivor of the accident, Mary, accepts a job in a new town as a church organist where she is repeatedly troubled by visions of a nearby abandoned carnival and a smiling white-faced man with dark rimmed eyes. One of the most atmospherically eerie works of American horror cinema, the film garnered a significant cult following years after being released in 1962, and is essential for every horror collection.

programme.title: Last Man on Earth
programme.desc: Vincent Price plays a doctor who must try to single-handedly save the earth when a plague causes the rest of the human race to turn into Vampire Zombies.

programme.title: The Wasp Woman
programme.desc: A cosmetics queen develops a youth formula from jelly taken from queen wasps. She fails to anticipate the typical hoary side-effects. (BW)

programme.title: Night of the Living Dead (1968)
programme.desc: "Night of the Living Dead" opens with chaos - the brains of the recently deceased have become mysteriously reanimated, causing the dead to rise and feed on human flesh. While visiting their father's grave, Barbra (Judith O'Dea) and her brother Johnny (Russell Streiner) are attacked by a strange shuffling man. Barbra runs into a farmhouse where she encounters Ben (Duane Jones), and they must find a way to save themselves from the horde of zombies. George Romero's "Night of the Living Dead" is hailed as one of the most influential horror films of all time - inspirational, thought provoking, and most importantly, terrifying!

programme.title: Invasion USA
programme.desc: THEY PUSH A BUTTON AND VAST CITIES VANISH BEFORE YOUR VERY EYES! A group of Americans are gathered at a New York bar when they discover that their country in under a Soviet invasion. They each return to their respective lives to see how they can each use their skills to stop the attacks before its too late.

programme.title: Dementia 13 (1963)
programme.desc: Written and directed by a 24-year-old Francis Ford Coppola, "Dementia 13" centers on the dysfunctional Haloran family, who have converged at Haloran Castle to enact a morbid ritual in remembrance of Lady Haloran's (Ethne Dunn) deceased daughter, Kathleen (Barbara Dowling). Secrets shroud Kathleen's demise, and soon there is a mysterious interloper prowling the grounds with a big axe to grind. Genuinely engaging and well-photographed, "Dementia 13" is a bone-chilling horror classic sure to thrill horror enthusiasts and Coppola fans alike.

programme.title: Werewolf of Washington
programme.desc: This 1973 Horror-Comedy The Werewolf of Washington acts as a political spoof of The Wolf Man.

programme.title: Fear in the Night (1947)
programme.desc: I DIDN'T WANT TO DO IT, BUT...MY BRAIN WAS HANDCUFFED! Can a man commit MURDER in a dream?...Here is the spine­tingling, blood­freezing answer...different from any mystery you've ever seen!... Based on a story by Cornell Woolrich, the king of psychological suspense, Fear in the Night tells the tale of a man who dreams he killed someone, then suspects it was real! Paul Kelly, DeForest Kelley, and Ann Doran star in this chiller from award winning director Maxwell Shane (The Glass Wall, The Naked Street). How do you solve a murder, when the only clue is a nightmare?

programme.title: Ghosts on the Loose (1943)
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi and the East Side Kids team up in this "spook comedy" from Monogram Pictures. The kids are trying to fix up a house for a newlywed couple, but find the place to be filled with secret panels, and even some strange men who seem to be lurking in the shadows. Look for the usual members of the gang, including Leo Gorcey as Mugs, and Huntz Hall as Gimpy, with the lovely Ava Gardner in her first speaking role. As the original ad campaign said, "It's Chill-arious!"

programme.title: Sisters of Death

programme.title: The Big Hit-Run Killer
programme.desc: A truck kills an old lady and her little grandson at a crossing and drives away. The owner of the truck asserts that he let a man called Paul lend the truck for one hour, but he doesn't know the last name of this man or where he lives. The police must investigate all circumstances, but should Friday and Smith really spend lots of resources on trying to find a man they hardly believe exists at all?

programme.title: The Big Girl
programme.desc: The detectives try to track down a tall, beautiful woman who has been terrorizing the city by robbing men, beating them up and in some cases shooting them. Their job is made more difficult by the fact that there are many inconsistencies in the victims' reports.

programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Hands Across The Border (1944)

The cast also includes such favorites as Onslow Stevens and Guinn "Big Boy" Williams, while songs include "Hey Hey (It's a Great Day)," "Dreaming to Music," and "The Girl with the High Button Shoes." For movie buffs: The music for the title song, "Hands Across the Border," was composed by none other than Hoagy Carmichael!

programme.title: Wagon Wheels (1934)
programme.desc: Randolph Scott (Ride the High Country) stars as Clint Belmet, the leader of a wagon train on the way to Oregon. Along the route he and his crew deal with various hardships, including Indian attacks and a fellow named Murdock (Monte Blue) who is out to stop them at any cost. With a cast that includes the likes of Gail Patrick and Billy Lee, this adventure saga was based on a novel by the western master, Zane Grey (Riders of the Purple Sage, Fighting Caravans). Trivia note: The film's original title was Caravans West.

programme.title: The Yellow Rose of Texas (1944)
programme.desc: Fans of Roy Rogers and Dale Evans will relish this western adventure. It features no less than nine musical numbers! Songs include, "The Timber Trail," "Western Wonderland," "Lucky Me, Unlucky You," "Song of the Rover," and more. There's even a tune partly written by Cuban bandleader Xavier Cugat! In between songs, there's a plot about a robbery, with Roy playing an insurance investigator trying to solve the riddle of the missing money.

programme.title: Meet Dr. Christian (1939)
programme.desc: In the first installment of what would be an ongoing movie series, we meet the kindly Dr. Christian (Jean Hersholt) of River’s End, Minnesota. All he wants to do is to raise money for a new hospital, but he’s up against a mayor who would prefer to build a new highway through town. The mayor also thinks the good doctor is a bit old-fashioned in his methods. But when the mayor’s daughter is injured in an accident, who do you think gets the call?

programme.title: The Hanged Man
programme.desc: After a condemned gunfighter (Steve Forrest) survives his own hanging, he helps a young widow stop a pitiless land baron from taking her ranch. This television feature boasts a strong cast of recognizable characters, including Will Geer, Dean Jagger, and Cameron Mitchell. Director Michael Caffey would go on to work on such hit shows as Barnaby Jones and MacGyver.

programme.title: The Big Lift (1950)
programme.desc: "The Big Lift" is a true account of the Berlin Airlift, which provided food and supplies to the Western sector of Berlin during the Soviet's blockade of Berlin. Sgt. Danny MacCullough (Montgomery Clift) and his friend Sgt. Hank Kowalski (Paul Douglas) are among the Americans called upon to risk their lives to transport supplies to the desperate citizens. The grim war is soon left behind as budding romances emerge between two women and the soldiers. Director George Seaton filmed on location with actual military personnel in minor acting roles, making "The Big Lift" one of the most remarkable war films of all time.

programme.title: Six Gun Trail
programme.desc: Legendary cowboy star Tim McCoy stars as Captain William Carson, who along with his sidekick Magpie does battle with jewel thieves. It’s an action­filled drama of the West, with plenty of blazing guns and he­man adventure! There are a couple of songs, too, including “Moon Over the Plains” but they aren’t sung by Tim McCoy. He was too darned tough to sing!

programme.title: Man of Steel
programme.desc: Divided into three parts, the film starts out with a group of workers opposing capitalism, followed by a wilderness adventure, and ending with a group of teenagers who experiment with drugs and alchohol only to see the light through religion.

programme.title: Nancy Drew Reporter
programme.desc: The teen sleuth is at it again! This was Bonita Granville's second turn as Nancy, the high school reporter who was the subject of four Warner Bros films in the late 1930s. This time she’s helping a young woman accused of murder. When Nancy persuades her loyal neighbor Ted to help her, it's only a matter of time before the identity of the real killer is revealed. Directed by William Clemens (the man behind the memorable “Falcon” series), and starring the likes of John Litel, Dickie Jones, and Frankie Thomas, the movie is a feisty little mystery that will have you rooting for Nancy to solve another one!

programme.title: “Heading Up the Heavy Duties”
programme.desc: Short Industrial Training film produced by Jam Handy.

programme.title: Breakdown
programme.desc: Framed for murder, heavyweight boxer Terry Williams is sent to prison, but is released after a few years on good behavior. He becomes a championship contender and then, on the eve of the big fight, finds the man who can prove that he was framed for the crime for which he served time.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 17
programme.desc: Carol Burnett stars in a series of comedic sketches guest starring Trini Lopez and Ken Berry.

programme.title: Season 26 Episode 131
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Soldiers in Greasepaint
programme.desc: 1955 American documentary narrated by Celeste Holm about distributing army films.

programme.title: The Bird With the Crystal Plumage
programme.desc: An American expat in Rome witnesses an attempted murder at an art gallery. He soon learns that it's connected to an ongoing murder spree in the city, and decides to do his own investigation, despite being personally targeted by the killer.

programme.title: Doomsday Machine
programme.desc: The crew aboard Project Astra, a space mission to Venus, witness the Earth being destroyed. Now they must ponder the repopulation of the human race.

programme.title: Battle of the Worlds
programme.desc: A runaway asteroid dubbed "The Outsider" mysteriously begins orbiting the Earth and threatens it with lethal flying saucers.

programme.title: The Ape
programme.desc: Kindly Dr. Adrian (Boris Karloff) is on the verge of creating a polio serum. Unfortunately, in order to complete his experiment he needs spinal fluid from a recently deceased human. All seems hopeless, but when a wild ape escapes from a nearby circus, Dr. Adrian's research takes on a ghastly new dimension. Director William Nigh (Black Dragons, Desert Nights) helmed this Poverty Row thriller from a screenplay co­written by Hollywood legend Curt Siodmak (The Wolfman, I Walked With A Zombie). Who will you root for – the jungle beast, or the man of science?

programme.title: The Big Trunk
programme.desc: Three men are the suspects in the beating death of a former vaudevillian actress found in her apartment. The possible reason for her murder could be among the contents of an old steamer trunk which she kept locked in her room. Surveillance equipment is used to solve the mystery.

programme.title: The Big Shoplift (1954)
programme.desc: Friday and his partner try to find the person responsible for a number of retail store thefts.

programme.title: Step Child (1954)
programme.desc: The public defender searches for the truth when a stepdaughter accuses her stepmother of cutting her and locking her in a closet.

programme.title: A Modern Fagan (1954)
programme.desc: Matthews tries to catch the leader of a gang of criminals.

programme.title: The Warning (1958)
programme.desc: The police begin spreading the word that Mike can identify a pair of masked killers after he was forced to watch them kill a man. With this information out there, Mike and his father find themselves in danger.

programme.title: Profile of a Killer (1958)
programme.desc: After taken hostage following a bank robbery in which the owner was killed, Mike must find a way to stop the robber-turned-killer before he hurts anyone else.

programme.title: Climax
programme.desc: Terror ensues when a maniacal sailor goes on a killing spree.

programme.title: On The Rocks
programme.desc: Jerry and rival publisher, Ned Walters, try to bring a successful writer to their respective firms. When Ned’s wife drinks her husband’s drink, she suddenly dies after drinking poison.

programme.title: The Jane Cooper Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: The Story of Cutie Jaffe
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: The Jerry Lewis Show Special: June 8, 1957
programme.desc: In this 1957 TV Special, Jerry Lewis hosts a series of comedic acts guest starring Eydie Gorme, Nelson Riddle & his orchestra, Rowan & Martin and Jerry's father Danny Lewis, and his son Gary Lewis.

programme.title: Raiders of Old California
programme.desc: The end of the Mexican-American War finds a brazen U.S. Calvary captain and his men taking over a Spanish land grant. Albert C. Gannaway (The Badge of Marshall Brennan) directs an all-star cast including Jim Davis (Jock Ewing of Dallas), Arleen Whelan (Young Mr. Lincoln) and Lee Van Cleef (The Good, The Bad, and the Ugly). Also, look for appearances by legendary country & western stars Marty Robbins and Faron Young.

programme.title: Young Buffalo Bill (1940)
programme.desc: Roy Rogers stars in this highly fictionalized account of Bill Cody's life from director Joseph Kane (Dakota, Flame of Barbary Coast). What it lacks in accuracy is made up for with adventure, as well as and some of Roy's great cowboy songs, including 'Blow Breeze Blow', and 'Rollin' Down to Santa Fe'. Other stars include George 'Gabby' Hayes, Chief Thundercloud, and the lovely Pauline Moore (Young Mr. Lincoln, Charlie Chan at Treasure Island)

programme.title: Little Annie Rooney (1925)
programme.desc: Mary Pickford, the queen of the silent screen, stars as a tough young ragamuffin who protects her neighborhood from a dangerous street gang. You may wonder why a 33-year-old woman is playing a girl, but this is little Mary, as people liked her best – ready to fight at the drop of a hat! Noted film historian Kevin Brownlow hailed this movie as "remarkable... All the artistry, technical skill, and emotional impact of a medium only thirty years old shine triumphantly through." Can Mary save the day? You bet!

programme.title: The Frank Sinatra Timex Show
programme.desc: The Frank Sinatra Timex show presents Frank Sinatra, leading a fanfare of variety acts, featuring the likes of Bing Crosby, Dean Martin, and Mitzi Gaynor.

programme.title: Judge Priest (1934)
programme.desc: Widowed judge William "Billy" Priest (Will Rogers), a proud Confederate veteran, uses old-fashioned horse sense to bestow justice in a small town in the Post-Bellum Kentucky. He also has time to play matchmaker for his lovelorn nephew!

programme.title: Black Beauty
programme.desc: Anne Wheldon (Mona Freeman) is given a horse for her birthday. She names the horse "Black Beauty" and they develop a special bond.

programme.title: Girl on a Chain Gang
programme.desc: This Town Got Ways of Teaching You a Lesson! The directorial debut of famed exploitation producer and distributor Jerry Gross, "Girl on the Chain Gang" follows the story three young people who are framed, arrested, and thrown in prison by corrupt Southern police. Starring William Watson, Julie Ange, and Ron Charles.

programme.title: The Royal Bed
programme.desc: Lowell Sherman and Nance O'Neil star as King and Queen who face off over their daughter's prospective engagement.

programme.title: Impact (1949)
programme.desc: An unfaithful wife and her lover scheme to kill her husband, but things are turned upside down when the lover is unintentionally killed instead! Then, in the best noir tradition, the husband goes into hiding and lets his wife take the rap! With a stellar cast that includes Brian Donlevy, Ella Raines, and Anna Mae Wong, this little noir gem from director Arthur Lubin (The Spider Woman Strikes Back) takes us into the lives of people who are only one kiss away from murder!

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 18

programme.title: The Black Raven

Mr. Amos Bradford is the proprietor, and runs the hotel with his assistant Andy. A group of strangers, guest at the hotel, are thrust together and must contend with two murders and $50,000 in stolen money.

programme.title: Indestructible Man (1956)
programme.desc: This is the movie you saw as a kid but can’t remember the title! Lon Chaney Jr. stars as “Butcher” Benton, a con who goes to his execution vowing to kill his former partners in crime. When his corpse is inadvertently brought back to life during a scientific experiment, he makes good on his deadly promises! This oddball feature was directed by Jack Pollexfen, a former newspaperman turned screenwriter, whose credits include Daughter of Dr. Jekyll, and The Man From Planet X...

programme.title: Attack From Space

programme.title: Torture Ship

His plan is to learn about the criminal mind, and what better way than to...well, you know. Obviously, this isn’t the Love Boat! Victor Halperin (White Zombie) directed this tale based on a story by none other than Jack London. Sit back and enjoy. Just don’t let the man with the scalpel near your head!

programme.title: Attack of the Giant Leeches (1959)
programme.desc: Massive bloodsucking monsters are at large in this Drive-in schlock classic from producers Roger and Gene Corman. The legendary Yvette Vickers (Attack of the 50-foot Woman) stars along with Jan Shepard, Ken Clark, and some nasty giant leeches! Basically, they're just a bunch of actors in plastic costumes, but director Bernard Kowalski (Hot Car Girl, Night of the Blood Beast) made the most of his small budget. When the Cormans wouldn't hire a crew to push the camera raft while filming water scenes in the Pasadena Arboretum, Kowalski put on a bathing suit and did it himself!

programme.title: Moving Stories
programme.desc: A film, by Rob Fruchtman, Cornelia Ravenal, Mikael Södersten, Wendy Sax Six, about diverse dancers from the acclaimed Battery Dance Company who travel the world, working with youth who have experienced war, poverty, prejudice, sexual exploitation, and severe trauma as refugees. In India they work with girls rescued from sex trafficking and gender violence; in Romania, with gypsy kids from one of Europe's worst slums; in South Korea, with young North Koreans who risked their lives to escape; and in Iraq, with a gifted young Muslim dancer, fighting to survive. Incredibly, they have just one week to teach the tools of choreography and collaboration to kids who may be enemies, who may have been abused, who may be suspicious and fearful, so that they can create dances to perform for their communities. As they struggle to break through, the dancer-teachers confront their own frustrations. Yet their students respond in extraordinary ways - and as they prepare to perform in public in what seems an impossibly short time, both students and teachers experience surprising transformations, unlocking feelings and stories in wellsprings of creativity.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai‘i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho‘onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

programme.title: Never Quit

programme.title: The Billionaire
programme.desc: A gender-swapped independent film adaptation of George Bernard Shaw's classic play 'The Millionairess', transposed into a contemporary context of Gay Marriage and Asexuality, THE BILLIONAIRE follows a haughty and prudish young billionaire's quest for love, despite all the odds. The film is a throwback to Classic Hollywood films, stylistically and tonally.

programme.title: The Influencers
programme.desc: Six social media influencers compete for an exclusive brand deal with the latest millennial juice craze: Jücytox. As cameras capture each influencer IRL, the manicured versions they present to the world online begin to not just crumble, but implode before our eyes.

programme.title: Dropping The Soap
programme.desc: 2017 Emmy Winner, Jane Lynch, Best Actress in Web Series/Comedy. Shit's about to get real for the cast and crew of the long running (awful) soap opera "Collided Lives" when new Executive Producer Olivia Vanderstein arrives to shake things up.

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S1 E1-3 | Alice and Veronica attempt to tell band manager Karen that they've broken up - as a band and a couple. They quickly learn that breaking up is not an option. Alice and Veronica start work on their second album. Band manager Karen introduces a new collaborator: the former CB3 child star turned pop starlet Lulu St. Claire. Axis Records executive Richard shows up to hear Alice and Veronica's progress on their new album. Alice takes a step forward with Lulu.

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S1 E4-6 | Alice and Veronica prepare for a live interview. Veronica is shocked by a discovery. Veronica and Alice shoot a music video with an eccentric French Canadian music video director. Alice and Veronica crash Lulu's ultra lame birthday party replete with pop, chips, and weird uncles. Lulu attempts to keep her budding romance with Alice a secret from her religious parents while Veronica gets up to her usual disruptive antics.

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S1 E7-10 | Alice and Veronica head to the studio to work on the new album. After Karen informs Alice that Lulu will no longer be working on the new album, Alice realizes this might be the end of her and Lulu's relationship. Veronica attempts to win back Alice by writing the perfect song. Her writer's block leads to a downward spiral of shoplifting and booze only hours before she is set to accompany Brooklyn to prom. Alice confronts Veronica about her poor choices. Veronica wakes up to find The Ghost of Girlfriend's Past waiting to take her on a Dickensian journey through her past. Alice accompanies Brooklyn to her prom in Veronica's stead. Lulu shows up to the prom unannounced, as does another surprise guest.↵

programme.title: Dating My Mother
programme.desc: Unemployed and living in his New Jersey hometown, brash screenwriter Danny spends his days practicing yoga, sipping red wine, and power-walking with his mother Joan. But when she reveals she’s seeing another man, their version of domestic bliss comes crashing down. DATING MY MOTHER follows the intimate and tumultuous relationship between a single mother and her gay son as they navigate the dizzying world of online dating. While they search for their versions of Mr. Right, mother and son discover that sometimes you need to be apart in order to grow together.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Happy Birthday Marsha
programme.desc: Happy Birthday, Marsha! is a film about iconic transgender artist and activist, Marsha "Pay it No Mind" Johnson, and her life in the hours before she ignited the 1969 Stonewall Riots in New York City.

programme.title: BIFL
programme.desc: Expectations, different shades of intimacy, & what it really means to love someone.

programme.title: Scales
programme.desc: S1 E1/2/3 | Meet Remy, Gavin, and David living in Atlanta finding balance in their lives. Remy has been single for quite some time, but an unexpected run in, could potentially change his fate./Remy is going to everyone for advice, including 17-year old Dakota Keller. Meanwhile, problems are brewing at home for Gavin and Sheila and David gets a rude awakening from a stranger./A revolving door can allow you to come in and out. In this case, Remy's house happens to be the revolving door, but someone ends up getting stuck. Remy and Sean must deal with their past. Sheila takes control of a situation and confronts Remy. Kevin’s sister, Gloria arrives with an update on Kevin’s progress.

programme.title: For The Love Of Food
programme.desc: In this poignant and culturally reflective documentary, meet the movers and shakers behind the young and erupting food media industry.

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S1 | A Revry Original Reality Series, ‘Putting On’ follows a young entrepreneur, On Mekahel, as he struggles to launch his underwear line with his ex-boyfriend.

programme.title: I'm From Driftwood
programme.desc: Laverne Cox: I'm From Mobile/New Teacher Encounters Homophobia In Second Week/Coming Out Again To Grandma With Alzheimer's/Gender Bending And Runway Walking In A McDonald's Parking Lot/Homeless, Transgender And Finding Her Way/Trans Woman Sacrifices Everything To Finally Be Herself/Transgender High School Student Encounters Cyberbullying/A Broken Down Car, Matching Tattoos, And A Love Story/Agender Person Goes From Being Bullied In The Newark Projects To Gracing The Cover of French Vogue/ Alan Cumming: True Bisexual Stories S1 E1-10 | Laverne Cox remembers the bullying she experienced as a child, and how it's similar to the transphobia she experiences as an adult. Alexa moved from New York City to small-town Jackson, Mississippi, to teach at an under-priveleged school. After only two weeks in, Alexa had to challenge homophobia in the hallway, and had some surprising success. Megan's grandma was supportive and excited when she found out Megan was a lesbian. But after showing signs of Alzheimer's, Megan's grandma forgot and kept asking her if she was seeing any special boy. Megan received a special phone call from her grandma, though, that she'll remember forever. Jacob Tobia, activist for genderqueer, gender non-conforming, and transgender issues, bought a single pair of black pumps while organizing a Gender Nonconforming Day for their high school, a small act that would change the course of their life. After being kicked out of her home at 17, Angela Louis struggled with homelessness, abusive relationships, sex work, and depression, all while transitioning, but nothing could stop her from finding her own path and earning her diploma. Mila Jam had it all, or so she thought. Her drag persona, Britney Houston, had a massive YouTube following and she performed on a hit TV show in London. But she gave it all up so that she could finally live her truth as a woman and as herself. Olivia Page was brave enough to transition in high school. Unfortunately, a classmate decided to cyberbully her on Facebook. Olivia also had the support and kindness of a teacher who helped her through high school. A wild series of events led Sam to meeting the love of her life. Andre J. wants to tell you one thing: Love Yourself. That's how Andre went from being bullied in the projects to appearing on the cover of French Vogue. Alan Cumming remembers when he first felt an attraction to guys and how he came out to American media in a big way. - Externals

programme.title: Equality U
programme.desc: Equality U is a feature-length documentary following 34 young activists on the Soulforce Equality Ride. At some stops they're welcomed with open arms, at others they're arrested for trespassing or for simply attempting to open up a dialog. At every stop, they're connecting with young people who've often never met an openly gay, lesbian, bisexual or transgender person who is comfortable with who they are.

programme.title: TransMilitary
programme.desc: The 2018 SXSW Audience Award-winning feature film debut by Gabriel Silverman, Fiona Dawson, & Jamie Coughlin, TransMilitary follows the Emmy-nominated short film Transgender, at War and in Love. Around 15,500 transgender people serve in the U.S. military (notably the largest transgender employer in the U.S.), where they must conceal their gender identity because military policies ban their service. TransMilitary chronicles the lives of four individuals (Senior Airman Logan Ireland, Corporal Laila Villanueva, Captain Jennifer Peace & First Lieutenant El Cook) defending their country’s freedom while fighting for their own. They put their careers and their families’ livelihoods on the line by coming out as transgender to top brass officials in the Pentagon in hopes of attaining the equal right to serve. The ban was lifted in 2016, but with President Trump now trying to reinstate it, their futures hang in the balance once again.

programme.title: Femme
programme.desc: From executive producer Rachel Brosnahan (The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel), comes a hilarious and moving story of self-acceptance. After being rejected for being too Femme, Carson learns to embrace his truth by way of a drag queen fairy godmother.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E1-2 | Lucy is a “very good ally” who stares at her best friend Miranda…. a lot. They hatch a plan to start Gay Prom Royalty together to promote equality at their school. Miranda pays Lucy a visit on a day off from school. We get a glimpse into Lucy’s home life.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E3-4 | Lucy visits the Gay Straight Alliance to gain support for Gay Prom Royalty. She shares some personal secrets to old and new friends. Anita’s throwing a party and a surprise promposal! Lucy has social anxiety about it.

programme.title: Baby Steps
programme.desc: From Oscar-winning Producer Li-Kong Hsu (Ang Lee’s The Wedding Banquet, Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon, Eat Drink Man Woman) and Stephen Israel (Swimming With Sharks and G.B.F.), comes this multi-cultural comedy-drama, which takes a funny but honest look at gay family issues in complicated dynamo of a cross-generational Taiwanese and American family. Danny, a Taiwanese-American man, longs to have a baby with his American partner Tate, but their attempts at international surrogacy are complicated by Danny’s meddling mother, who wants to control every aspect of the process -- all the way from Taipei.

programme.title: Single Record
programme.desc: Aaron gets mild success by getting his song played on the radio and a record deal/Aaron’s apartment gets broken into and all of his original music is stolen.

programme.title: For Izzy
programme.desc: The lives of a recovering queer addict and her single mother change forever when they move in next door to a widowed father and his adult daughter with autism.

programme.title: Your Eyes On Me
programme.desc: Your Eyes on Me is a story about a drag queen named Gloria whose life changes when she meets Kandi, a drag virgin auditioning for her next show. As the bond develops between the two, their relationship takes an unexpected turn. Suddenly the past and the choices Gloria made as a young man become a stark reality.

programme.title: Amplify Voices
programme.desc: S1 E6 | We are beginning to realize that it is not enough to be an ally. It’s time now to educate ourselves and prepare to address and attack racism, transphobia, and homophobia head on.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Savannah is a ray of light in the LGBTQ+ youth community and she wants to be a Disney animator one day. She is a member of the Mormon church and has been all of her life however when Savannah came out to her to ward during a sacrament meeting a year ago, the Bishop had her microphone turned off, stopping her right before she had wrapped up her speech. She has since become an advocate for LGBTQ+ teens.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Cody (Elton Cray) is a professional musician & rapper. We did an initial interview with him in his home, then visited with him almost 10 months later at one of his shows. An interesting and passionate man who speaks his mind, Cody's music is about his struggles with himself and others around him who have been indifferent to how he identifies.

programme.title: America In Transition
programme.desc: S1 E1 | After growing up misunderstood in India, Nina fell in love with another trans woman in the United States. Facing the threat of deportation, Nina and her love continue to fight for space to live and flourish when no place feels safe.

programme.title: Scrum
programme.desc: The lives of a self-assured Canadian jock, a rookie Irish backpacker and a stoic Japanese outsider change when they vie for a position in the grueling Bingham Cup.

programme.title: Rave Train
programme.desc: Rave Train is a video series that features live EDM DJ and Artist performances with a diverse range of dancers from the Rave culture. SOUL TRAIN meets EDM; Rave Train brings movement to sound with the latest dance styles with today’s upcoming Electronic Music artists.

programme.title: Engaged
programme.desc: ENGAGED is a short romantic comedy that follows Darren (Daniel K. Isaac), who keeps trying – and failing – to propose to his boyfriend Elliot (Ryan Jamaal Swain). When their relationship is put into an uncomfortable spotlight during a friend’s outrageous engagement party, Darren realizes he actually might be self–sabotaging himself due to unresolved insecurities about his sexuality.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S1 E5 | Enrique, Juliana and Lianna discuss bisexuality. Anthony Ramos joins The Q Agenda to talk about the goals of GLAAD and how they work with celebrities to make sure their Q agenda gets passed. Filmmaker and dreamer Jorge Xolalpa opens up about coming out twice, once for his sexuality and again as a DACA Dreamer.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S1 E6 | Actor Erik Liberman joins The Q Agenda to discuss the importance of onscreen LGBTQ representation, and promote his book on the iconic actress Jayne Mansfield. Actor Darryl Stephens from Noah’s Ark, the first LGBTQ show with a majority black cast, shares his experiences on the show and the state of LGBTQ media representation.

programme.title: CONTRACORRIENTE
programme.desc: Miguel is a fisherman in a tiny Peruvian village where traditions run deep. He is married to the lovely Mariela and about to be a father, but has a secret love affair with Santiago, a painter, who is ostracized by the town because he's gay. After a tragic accident occurs, Miguel must choose between sentencing Santiago to eternal torment or doing right by him and, in turn, revealing their relationship to Mariela and the entire village.

programme.title: DIA NARANJA

programme.title: Canada Cultivation and Mushroom Editing
programme.desc: In early May, we had Mydecine (NEO: MYCO) (OTCMKTS: MYCOF) CSO Rob Roscow on the Dales Report to talk about their 2a clinical trials. Today we have Damon Michaels with us to discuss some of the recent news that’s come out for Mydecine including Health Canada’s approval of the expansion of their cultivation facilities here in Canada. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Canadian expansion means that Mydecine has “instant access” and allows them to supply clinical trials says Michaels - - The possibility of editing mushrooms - - Mydecine facility in Canada probably won’t scale to meet a commercial need, says Michaels - - The roadmap for the next 12 months? Proving efficacy and safety – and looking at protocols

programme.title: How the Psychedelic Industry Can Help Mental Health
programme.desc: Last month we had Dr. Mike Hart for an interview with The Dales Report. Dr. Hart is the Host of Heart to Hart Podcast and a medical doctor at the Ready To Go Clinic, offering treatments to patients that involve cannabis and ketamine. We’re thrilled to have Hart back with us again to discuss the different psychedelic compounds and how they can impact mental health, plus how the industry is benefitting from cannabis’ legalization. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - The psychedelic molecule psilocybin affects mental health in part by breaking up your default mode network - - Psychedelics’ perception benefitting from cannabis’ legalization - - Both cannabis and psychedelic compounds have an impact on empathy and improved mental health - - COVID and financial worry is taking a toll

programme.title: MDMA-Assisted Therapy for PTSD
programme.desc: A new report just released this week by Nature Medicine has a lot of players in both medicine and the psychedelics industry talking. MDMA and other psychedelics like psilocybin have been under scrutiny lately as a possible avenue of treatment for not only PTSD but mental health issues generally. Dr. Mike Hart is back to chat again with us about that report on MDMA-Assisted therapy for severe PTSD. Dr. Hart is the Host of Heart to Hart Podcast and a medical doctor at the Ready To Go Clinic in London, Ontario. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - PTSD very difficult to treat - - Hart says that MDMA-Assisted therapy works because the psychedelic reduces ego - - Hart feels legalization within a year unlikely, and other MDMA-assisted therapy studies will improve

programme.title: American MC - E03 - "Hell Ride" with Angels
programme.desc: Everyone knows the name "Hells Angels." They are the undisputed leaders of the "One-Percenter's" - the "Motorcycle Clubs" - the "M.C.'s." When a group of Hells Angels walk into a bar where the Ice Cream Men From Hell are drinking, Baker decides to send Moody up to say hi. The HA are there to support and attend The Florence Prison Run so they tell the ICMFH they can ride along "if they can stay up, they can keep up." No one gets an invitation to ride with the Hells Angels. The ICMFH aren't going to mess up this opportunity - or will they?

programme.title: American MC - E04 - The Longest Day's Ride
programme.desc: After crashing a Hawaiian Tropic Girl's photo shoot, The Ice Cream Men From Hell finally arrive at The Florence Prison Run and find out the real meaning of honor and brotherhood. They are flying high from their ride with the Hells Angels, but the high-speeds are causing dissension among the members - and Kevin turns in his colors. A visit to historic Tombstone gives Baker pause and makes him re-think the ICMFH patch and asks the members to vote on giving it up. Is this the end of the club?

programme.title: American Cafe
programme.desc: American Cafe is a look into Cafe Racer motorcycle culture in the United States. Transplanted from Europe, the term "Cafe Racer" describes both a type of motorcycle as well as the personality of those who ride them. American Cafe tells the story of this culture in America by following two motorcyclists attempting to build Cafe Racers to ride in the Slimey Crud Motorcycle Gang Cafe Racer Run.

programme.title: Bike and Builder - S1 E02 - Keino Sasaki

programme.title: Mooneyes : Hot Rod Custom Show 2012
programme.desc: After the cars here in, the bikes were next. This year there were nine motorcycles in total so it was decided to bring them in three at a time. The first group featured Born Free 4 Best of Show winner Matt Olsen on his 1947 H-D Knucklehead, Jeff Wright of Church of Choppers with his personal custom built 1978 H-D Shovelhead and Scott Jones of Noise Cycles with Chaka Khan, a 1978 H-D Shovelhead.

programme.title: Mooneyes : Hot Rod Custom Show 2013
programme.desc: There are a lot of custom bike shows around some large some small, seems to be that a lot of people think their bike is "custom" because they chose a custom paint job, custom grips, pegs and bars from the catalogue provided by the manufacturer. Sure there are all levels of custom from very mild to extreme but for me what makes a custom is the heart, hand and imagination , of the owner / builder, it is not necessary to spend a million bucks, all it takes is passion! At the Mooneyes Hot Rod and Custom show held each December in Yokohama the home town of Mooneyes Japan, Shige Suganuma and his crew of dedicated custom lovers put an enormous effort into bringing you the best of Custom Motorcycles and Cars from around the globe for your viewing pleasure. Passion and imagination are on display on a massive scale, with 650 bikes 250 cars on display and each one jaw droppingly fabulous, the only problem is that the show only runs for one day, you will leave exhausted with aching feet and a brain buzzing with sensory overload, Mooneyes is something you have to see before you die!

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.
