programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Samoa: Tattoo Heritage
programme.desc: The tattooing practiced in Samoa is not comparable to the fashionable trend in Europe. In Samoa, tattooing is above all a rite signifying that the individual belongs to a group, and it is extremely painful. The more painful it is, the more Stivi approaches the state of a real, accomplished man.

programme.title: Haiti: The Carnival of Specters
programme.desc: Every year in Jacmel, on the southern coast of Haiti, festivities take on an intensity not found elsewhere. Haitians do not depict dream-like characters in their parades, but instead, monsters or specters. This is a way for them to deal with the difficulties of the past, and those of the present.

programme.title: India: Festival of Colors
programme.desc: Simple colored powder can break down the barriers between people. Since the dawn of antiquity, to mark the spring equinox, the whole of India celebrates Holi, the festival of colors. During this celebration, Indians of all castes throw colored powder in the faces of people they meet.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: S9E1 - Oaxaca's Most Magical Holiday
programme.desc: Rick takes us on a remarkable journey through Oaxaca City during the revered Dia de Los Muertos (Day of the Dead) holiday. Much preparation for the celebration takes place in October, and Rick gives us an insider’s look at the fiesta.

programme.title: S9E2 - Oaxaca's Live-Fire Cooking
programme.desc: Everything tastes better when cooked over a fire, at least that is the Oaxacan credo. From soup to barbacoa, fiery embers influence the flavor of Oaxaca’s food in just the right ways. Join Rick in Oaxaca, San Felipe Usila, and Zaachilla.

programme.title: S9E3 - Off the Beaten Path in Huatulco
programme.desc: Mexico's beaches glimmer with pristine perfection. Chef Rick Bayless takes us off the beaten path to find great food and even better beaches such as Playa Chahue and Playa Principal. You would be well-advised to follow his lead.

programme.title: S9E4 - Artisan Mescal
programme.desc: Mescal is experiencing a renaissance in Mexico and throughout the United States. Journey with Rick to witness firsthand how an Oaxacan distiller handcrafts this fine spirit renowned for its rich, smoky complexity and brightness.

programme.title: S9E5 - Oaxaca, the Land of Seven Moles
programme.desc: So many moles, so little time. Rick will focus on two moles while visiting the Seasons of My Heart Cooking School on the outskirts of Oaxaca City to explore Black Mole and Green Mole with school owner Susana Trilling and her students.

programme.title: S9E6 - Delicious Eco-Tourism
programme.desc: Ever on a quest to learn more about food, Rick even vacations with a food-oriented agenda. Join him in the mountains of Finca Las Nieves, with its artisanal coffee production and organic gardens, and learn about sustainable gardening.

programme.title: S9E7 - The Kernel of Deliciousness
programme.desc: The variety of corns available in Oaxaca boggles the mind and the taste buds. Rick introduces us to Amado Ramirez Leyva who believes that corn, domesticated some 9,000 years ago in Mexico, represents the very foundation of Mexican culture.

programme.title: S9E8 - Mercado Madness
programme.desc: “You are what you eat.” Brillat Savarin’s statement fuels Rick’s tour of the 21 de Noviembre market in downtown Oaxaca. We uncover the incredibly rich culture of the market and its role in the daily lives and meals of the local population.

programme.title: S9E9 - Oaxacan Cheese Primer
programme.desc: In Mexico, cheese is all about freshness, and fresh cheese is exactly what Rick has found in the village of Rojas where he and two local women turn uber-fresh milk from alfalfa-fed cows into queso fresco and salty quesillo (string cheese).

programme.title: S9E10 - Puerto Escondido: Living the Dream
programme.desc: Ever dream of renting a space with a kitchen in Mexico just to cook all the fresh fish you can eat? Rick lives the dream at Hotel Villas Carrizalillo in Puerto Escondido. With few culinary tools, and fresh ingredients, it is time to feast.

programme.title: S9E11 - Chocolate & Coffee from Bean to Cup
programme.desc: In Mexico, hot chocolate and coffee are equally enjoyed. The Seasons of My Heart Cooking School explains the roasting process from two perspectives, while the Finca Las Nieves Coffee Plantation offers a look into organic coffee production.

programme.title: S9E12 - Bringing Oaxaca Home
programme.desc: The once unknown state of Oaxaca is now on the savvy traveler’s hit list. Its capital is one of Mexico’s most enjoyable colonial cities. Rick takes the spirit of Oaxaca home, and with a group of friends, creates a dinner sure to transport.

programme.title: S9E13 - Oaxaca's Top Chefs
programme.desc: Oaxaca has long been known for its seven moles, unparalleled home-cooking, and remarkable market fare. Lately, its restaurant reputation has skyrocketed, too. Deservedly so. Rick visits four of the top chef contenders in Oaxaca City.

programme.title: S8E1 - Mediterranean Baja
programme.desc: The Baja California peninsula boasts a climate reminiscent of the Mediterranean Sea. Rick makes tacos with ingredients from the gardens of the Rancho La Puerta spa, and meets up with Chefs Miguel Angel Guerrero Yagues and Jair Tellez.

programme.title: S8E2 - Tijuana Taco Crawl
programme.desc: Three local Tijuana foodies take Rick on a taco crawl. Experience arrachera tacos, suadero tacos, sauteed and fried shrimp tacos, steamed tacos, and smoked salmon tacos. At home, Rick creates a taco feast for a casual backyard cookout.

programme.title: S8E3 - Cooking on the Sea of Cortez
programme.desc: Rick is always up for a cooking challenge, and after a day on the waters of the Sea of Cortez, Rick grills dinner for the group on the beach of Espiritu Santo Island. To stock up on supplies Rick shops in the La Paz market for ingredients.

programme.title: S8E4 - Presenting: World-Class Wines of Baja
programme.desc: Join Rick and winemaker Hugo d’Acosta as they toast the world-class wines of Baja California Norte. Hugo first introduces Rick his Casa de Piedra wines before moving on to Tres Mujeres, L.A. Cetto, and the San Rafael Winery.

programme.title: S8E5 - Eat Like a Local in Los Cabos
programme.desc: Ever travel to a tourist mecca and wonder what the locals eat? Join Rick and his friend Hugo to find the best Mexican food in Los Cabos. First stop is the municipal market in San Jose del Cabo, then they enjoy carnitas at Los Michoacanos.

programme.title: S8E6 - A Delicious Feast in Magdalena Bay
programme.desc: Rick and local guide Luis Garduno of REDTours venture out on a skiff to learn about sustainable fishing on Magdalena Bay. They catch up with local lobster fishermen and clam divers and follow that up with shore lunch on Isla de Magdalena.

programme.title: S8E7 - Cooking in Wine Country
programme.desc: Ever dream of owning a winery? Don and Tru Miller made their dreams come true when they built Adobe Guadalupe. Rick’s dream of cooking in their stunning kitchen, with its handmade wood-fired oven, comes true this season. Dream on.

programme.title: S8E8 - Tijuana Round Table
programme.desc: There is a long heritage of good food in Tijuana. The city has an amazing taco, culture and is the birthplace of the Caesar salad. Today, Tijuana boasts one of the top culinary schools in the country and some of the best chefs in Mexico.

programme.title: S8E9 - Extraordinarily Delicious Ensenada
programme.desc: Fish tacos embody Ensenada’s history: Fresh fish from pristine waters encased in crispy batter influenced by Asian immigrants, topped with Spanish-inspired creamy sauces, wrapped in a very Mexican corn tortilla, and spiked with chile.

programme.title: S8E10 - Mexican Microbrews and Pub Fare
programme.desc: Many of us experienced our first Mexican beer on a beach with a squeeze of lime. Now we are happy to see a beer revolution rumbling in the Baja peninsula. Rick takes us from the Tecate brewery to the Tijuana brewery. Salud-

programme.title: S8E11 - Sustainable Aquaculture in the Rich Waters of Ensenada
programme.desc: Two of Ensenada’s best chefs, Benito Molina, and Alain Genchi, join Rick for a lesson in mollusk farming. Juan Carlos Lapuente takes the trio to the rich coastal waters to see oyster and mussel farming and learn why these waters thrive.

programme.title: S8E12 - Todos Santos Magic
programme.desc: There is magic in the charming Baja town of Todos Santos. It all starts at the roadside bar Art and Beer. Then Rick checks into the Hotel California before meeting with Sergio Jaurequi, as well as Chefs Dona Ramona and Dany Lamote.

programme.title: S8E13 - Baja Beach House Cooking
programme.desc: Rick introduces us to some of Los Cabos’ top chefs and their restaurants, then cooks dinner for them at a luxurious beach house. At dinner, Rick, Margarita, and the local chefs discuss the philosophy of cooking and dining together.

programme.title: Darwin Northern Territory
programme.desc: In Darwin, Jason swims in the Crocodile Tank and visits Litchfield National Park. He also goes heli-pubbing, savours the delicious barra burger, then catches, and cooks, black pepper mud crab. Delicious!

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Malta
programme.desc: A delightful Mediterranean climate, fantastic beaches, and fascinating historic sites only begin to describe the Maltese experience. Few places in the world possess a more exquisite coastline. The HBO series, "Game of Thrones," filmed portions of the series in Malta's capital city of Valletta.

programme.title: Dublin
programme.desc: At the confluence of Muir Eireann and the Irish Sea on Ireland’s East Coast stands the capital city of Dublin. Join Laura McKenzie as she enjoys the perfect pint at Gravity Bar atop Guinness Brewery, explore Dublin Castle, and become acquainted with The Four Seasons Dublin.

programme.title: Paris
programme.desc: There is more than enough to keep you busy in Paris. Historic sites such as the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Picasso Museum, and Paris Opera House only get you started. Tuileries Garden and Paris Beach offer a unique way to relax and have fun, and Sacre-Coeur offers a 360-degree view of city.

programme.title: Los Angeles
programme.desc: Rent a Rolls Royce and roll through L.A. in style. When you hit Hollywood and Vine you know you are in the city’s heart, as the Pantages Theater, Capitol Records Building, Grauman's Chinese Theatre, and Kodak Theater greet you. Get the skinny on everything Beverly Hills and visit Olvera Street.

programme.title: Prague
programme.desc: Explore the heart of Bohemia as we join Laura in Prague. Visit Prague Castle, the Charles Bridge, and the Jewish Quarter. Gothic Loket Castle is a short, scenic drive away from the city and worth the tour. Next up the must-see spa town of Karlovy Vary.

programme.title: Britain's Historic Countryside
programme.desc: First stops are Camden Market and Notting Hill Gate. Enjoy a treat as Laura escorts you to the birthplace of pomp and circumstance, Buckingham Palace. Then mosey down to Windsor Castle before taking on London with Big Ben and Tower Bridge.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Delhi and Agra, India
programme.desc: From the serene beauty of one man's architectural love poem to a woman, the Taj Mahal, to the crowded alleys of downtown New Delhi, India is a feast for the senses. Maxa discovers temples straight out of Disneyland and consults a street astrologer who tells him he will live a long life.

programme.title: Rajasthan, India
programme.desc: Tour the royal rooms behind the sandstone walls of the Mehrangarh Fort, perched high above the city of Jodhpur. In the countryside outside of Jodhpur, villagers, who have never seen a Westerner, invite Rudy Maxa into their homes, and the maharajah of Jodhpur explains why his palace is now a hotel.

programme.title: Istanbul, Turkey
programme.desc: In Istanbul, evidence of historical invasion exists everywhere. From the Romans to the Ottomans, this tumultuous city has seen it all, and its architecture, cuisine, and customs reflect that reality. Tour the Grand Bazaar, Topkapi Palace, the Hagia Sophia, the Blue Mosque, and the Spice Market.

programme.title: Turkey's Turquoise Coast
programme.desc: Ancient towns of Ephesus, Antalya, Myra and Dalyan dot the Turkish coast, tempting visitors to step back in time when lavish Roman homes and markets dotted the landscape. Boarding a gulet, the traditional wooden Turkish boat, for a Blue Cruise, Rudy departs from the popular seaside town of Bodrum.

programme.title: Bangkok, Thailand
programme.desc: Rudy takes you off the beaten path into the quiet, residential klongs, or canals, of Bangkok. Marvel at the Emerald Buddha, visit the city's fresh markets, join locals offering incense and flowers at colorful outdoor shrines, celebrate the king's 80th birthday with an all-night party, and more.

programme.title: Thailand, The Golden Triangle
programme.desc: The saffron robes of Buddhist monks, the vivid colors of local blossoms, and the brilliant emerald of rice fields make the Golden Triangle a magical corner of the world. Join Rudy as he takes mahout lessons and gets soaked steering his elephant into the river that separates Thailand from Burma.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: France's Via Aquitania
programme.desc: Follow the Via Aquitania, an ancient Roman road that connected a network of cities and was the main trade route between the Mediterranean Sea and the Atlantic Ocean. Traces of the region’s history abound and will become clearer to you the more you hear the people who love this land speak of it.

programme.title: The Road of the Nomadic Soul: from Kyrgyzstan to Tajikistan
programme.desc: Your journey begins with a trek from Bishkek, the capital of Kyrgyzstan, to Lake Issyk Kul. Then, head through the mountains and pasture where shepherds live. On your way to Tajikistan, you will cross the Trans-Alay mountains in the Western Pamirs populated by the Kyrgyz people of nomadic tradition.

programme.title: Philippines - The Unexplored Archipelago
programme.desc: The Philippines consist of roughly 7,000 islands, including the island of Palawan, one of the wildest islands in the world. Still very undeveloped and traditional in its ways, Palawan's jungles, mountains, abundant wildlife, and beaches make it one of the most biodiverse islands in the Philippines.

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Brazil - A Preserved Beauty
programme.desc: Fernando de Noronha is an archipelago of 21 islands and islets in the Atlantic Ocean. The wild, natural beauty found above and below the sea are the main attractions of the region, where you can observe sea tortoises, dolphins, albatrosses, and some of the most stunning beaches on Earth.

programme.title: Egypt - Water And Sand
programme.desc: Siwa is an island-oasis of fire-torched skies in the middle of the Egyptian desert where The Great Sand Sea comes to rest at the foot of an oasis of date palms. Bordered by two lakes of turquoise blue, travelers find themselves at an oasis that is authentically North African.

programme.title: The Mediterranean Dream - Part 1
programme.desc: Your Mediterranean dream begins in Gibraltar and its stunning panoramic views. Revive your spirit in Carcassonne, Cannes, and Provence, France, and dream onward into Italy and explore Florence, Rome, and Venice. Finally, tour one of the most prominent vacation spots on the Mediterranean, Dubrovnik.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new releases

programme.title: Renaissance Europe
programme.desc: Travelers adore Italy, and Italy adores the Renaissance. In this historical half-hour, we follow Western Europe's transitiical sites and museums in favor of a trip--or a day--just for fun.

programme.title: Europe's Getaways
programme.desc: A key attraction of travel on any continent, including Europe, is that 30 minutes outside any city exists a getaway unlike any you will find on the globe. Truly unique locations that resonate with history and significance. Here, we explore a few such places.

programme.title: Ireland's West Coast
programme.desc: Our trip to Ireland's west coast begins in Galway, Europe's fastest growing city, shopping for Irish crystal and Celtic jewelry. Then it is a salt-sprayed trip to the fabled Aran Islands where we reach breathless heights at a Stone Age fort and ferret out traditional hand-knit sweaters.

programme.title: S8E12 - Berlin
programme.desc: While visiting Berlin's powerful sights — moving memorials, top-tier museums, surviving bits of communist and fascist days — we'll take time to revel in its vibrant social scene.

programme.title: Sydney New South Wales
programme.desc: In Sydney, Jason takes part in some cooking at the award-winning Marque restaurant and meets with an up-and-coming pastry chef at The Blackstar Pastry. For some fun activities, he tries grape stomping and quad biking.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Travel Thru History
programme.desc: In this episode we visit the Kennedy Space Center located on Florida's famous Space Coast. We will speak to NASA engineers about the past, present and future of American space travel, as well as take a look at the attractions K.S.C. has to offer.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: Hidden Gems of
programme.desc: The world-class attractions and top-level resorts at both Walt Disney World and Disneyland are familiar to millions around the world. There is also a hidden side to Disney Parks that are unfamiliar to many, a side that is undiscovered... Until now. Take a vacation into the unknown with Disney.

programme.title: Hidden
programme.desc: Three athletes, three elements, three friends. All believing in their own path in life. Each crossing the same road full of doubts, while harnessing their efforts and hunger for a sport, for a job, for a fire that, at this moment, ceases to be hidden.

programme.title: Ireland: Part 1
programme.desc: At the right angles, Ireland can be bold and striking. Water’s unmistakable voice permeates around you as the sounds and rhythms of nature awaken your spirit in Galway Bay, as you gaze out upon the Cliffs of Moher, and more.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Bangkok
programme.desc: Bangkok is a city of sensory overload. Visit the majestic Wat Arun, or The Temple of the Dawn, a Buddhist Temple along the Chao Phraya River. In the heart of Bangkok lies the Grand Palace where visitors gaze upon the Emerald Buddha, and shop the Weekend Market for something authentically Thai.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Once the capital of the world, join Laura in Rome. Travel Rome's oldest road, the Appian Way, and behold St. Peter's Basilica, an Italian Renaissance church that will touch your heart and soul, especially when you view Michelangelo's Pieta. That, and myriad other glorious sites, await you in Rome.

programme.title: Edinburgh
programme.desc: Edinburgh Castle stands boldly atop Castle Rock. Visit St. Margaret's Chapel, the oldest building in Edinburgh, and become acquainted with the legend of Greyfriars Bobby. The Royal Mile and the Grassmarket will keep you busy and fed and tour the waters in luxury aboard the HMY Britannia.

programme.title: Greek Islands
programme.desc: Laura believes the Greek Islands are the perfect destination for a family vacation. Take the island of Hydra, for instance. No cars, trucks, nor buses are allowed, and there is virtually no crime. Cruise by the volcanic island of Poros in private mega-yacht O'Pari before arriving on Aegina Island.

programme.title: San Francisco
programme.desc: Stroll down Grant Street with Laura into the heart of America's largest Chinatown. Bike, drive, or walk across the Golden Gate Bridge, the city's most recognizable landmark. Finally, Fisherman's Wharf offers day trips all wrapped into one fun location.

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: Enter 12 miles of enclosing walls, 26 acres of roof, and over 2,000 windows and experience the royal Palace of Versailles. If you are looking for some good ole' fun, then you will enjoy Parc Asterix. Place Vendome is the top spot for high-end merchandise.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: South Africa
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa knows that an adventurous safari is a wonderful way to experience South Africa. Get up-close-and-personal with lions, giraffes, elephants, and dozens of other animals in their natural habitat, thanks to robust preservation laws in place.

programme.title: Edinburgh and the Scottish Highlands
programme.desc: Climb the ramparts of Edinburgh Castle. Tee up at the world's most famous golf course, St. Andrews. Tour Deward's whiskey distillery. Stroll Stirling's historic battlefields of Braveheart fame. And, sail the bonny banks of legendary Loch Lomond.

programme.title: London
programme.desc: Rudy answers London's call with an expert tour of its traditional sights and contemporary, cutting-edge attractions. In London's breathtaking countryside you will find mythic castles, the real Alice in Wonderland's candy store, Jane Austen's house, and the mysterious megaliths of Stonehenge.

programme.title: Uzbekistan
programme.desc: In one of his series' most colorful episodes, Maxa takes viewers along the Silk Road in a country that is an emerging economy in Central Asia, Uzbekistan. Marvel at eye-popping mosques built centuries ago, and Rudy joins a family for the preparation of the national dish of "plov."

programme.title: Cape Town
programme.desc: Cape Town is a nexus of cultures in a setting so stunning it is called “Africa's Riviera." Where else in the world can you wake up in a cosmopolitan city, spend the afternoon with penguins, ride a funicular to the edge of the continent, and watch the sun set from a beach with a glass of wine?

programme.title: Garden Route
programme.desc: The Garden Route takes you along a rugged, gorgeous South African coastline. Surfers brave enormous waves and exotic birds watch visitors climb serpentine paths that rise above the coast amid seaside resort towns. Also, visit South Africa's lush wine country in the village of Franschhoek.

programme.title: Korea
programme.desc: From the bustling city of Seoul with its 10 million residents to the country's quite countryside, South Korea is a traveler’s paradise. With their misty mountain temples and the uber-modern cities, Koreans mix an abiding sense if history and traditions with a zeal to achieve global success.

programme.title: Best of the National Parks
programme.desc: Each year millions from around the world visit America's national parks, lured by images of lands of wonder beyond expression. This exhilarating program reveals the very best locations in America’s national parks to gaze at geysers, spot wildlife, mountain climb, spelunk, and even tie the knot.

programme.title: Germany's Via Julia
programme.desc: Discover the ancient Roman military road Via Julia that made rapid travel from Lutetia (now Paris) to Constantinople (now Istanbul) possible. Meet the people who keep the memories of this ancient route intact, and who do their utmost to keep the sacred traditions of their ancestors alive.

programme.title: The Road of Money: Mexico to the U.S.A.
programme.desc: Upon landing in Mexico centuries ago the Spanish immediately found silver. The Spanish then constructed a road 3,000 km long to transport the silver from the mines, a road full of hopes, but also riddled with pitfalls and danger. Explore this ancient road from Mexico to the southern United States.

programme.title: The Bahamas - The Heart of the Ocean
programme.desc: As the first lands of the New World to be discovered by Europeans, the Bahamas have always attracted sailors and adventurers. Fed by the warm, nutrient-rich currents of the Gulf Stream, their shallow waters offer today's travelers a crystal-clear sea teeming with marine life.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: Mexico - A Desert Between Two Seas
programme.desc: The Baja Peninsula juts out into the Pacific Ocean like an icicle. The dazzling arid peninsula is a succession of sunset-kissed beaches and trickling creeks. Each year, millions of whales come to reproduce in the preserved waters of the peninsula that their whale ancestors knew so well.

programme.title: South Africa - A Rainbow Nation
programme.desc: With its wide-open spaces and pristine coastline, the province of KwaZulu-Natal has become one of South Africa's ecotourism havens. Away from the carefree atmosphere of its beaches, become a privileged witness to KwaZulu-Natal's well-preserved flora, fauna, and wildlife, possibly “The Big Five?”

programme.title: The Mediterranean Dream - Part 2
programme.desc: Your Mediterranean dream continues in Kotor, Montenegro, an exquisite city set upon the Adriatic Sea. Experience the essence of Greece in Mykonos, Athens, and Santorini, and tour the historic city of Istanbul, Turkey, and Egypt is where some of humankinds most incredible creations still stand.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: France's Burgundy and Loire Regions
programme.desc: The Burgundy region boasts top French wines, romantic canals, Romanesque churches, and world-renowned French cuisine. We base in the small town of Beaune and learn about its history of exceptional winemaking. Add a wondrous hot-air balloon ride over the verdant Loire Valley to the itinerary.

programme.title: Berlin
programme.desc: With world-class cultural sites, dynamic new architecture and unstoppable energy, Berlin is a city on the move. We visit the museums - the ancient treasures of the Pergamon and the Egyptian museum, German Expressionism at the Neue Nationalgalerie and the newly designed Jewish Museum.

programme.title: Munich and Bavaria
programme.desc: Munich's lively Marienplatz pulses with outdoor cafes, shoppers, street musicians, and happy tourists. At the famous Hofbrauhaus sample Bavarian beer and kick up your heels with Schuhplattler dancers clad in lederhosen. Next stop is the Residenz, the family palace built by the Wittlesbachs.

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: Undiscovered
programme.desc: In Disneyland, walk in Walt Disney’s footsteps and discover the secret spots he created. Step inside the newly constructed Disneyland Dream Suite – a magical space in the park’s New Orleans Square. Just around the corner is another secret spot that very few people even have access to – Club 33.

programme.title: The Glacier Express and Gornergrat-Bahn
programme.desc: Go sightseeing on the Glacier Express, an extraordinary railway journey high into the Swiss Alps across 291 bridges, through 91 tunnels, and across the Oberalp Pass at the highest point (2,033 meters, or 6,670 feet, above sea level), and, visit the iconic Matterhorn on the Gornergrat-Bahn.

programme.title: Ireland: Part 2
programme.desc: The gentle side of Ireland shines through in five peaceful locations in Doolin and Kilkenny, where the ancient and the modern meld beautifully together. Nature’s music serenades you as you are reminded of the joys of fresh air, wide open spaces, and the majesty of humanity.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: London
programme.desc: London has played a key role in world affairs for centuries, and as you stroll throughout this magnificent city, history comes to life before your eyes. Buckingham Palace, Campden Market, Covent Garden, the Tower of London, and Cliveden House are just the beginning of the places you will visit.

programme.title: Amsterdam
programme.desc: Whether by foot, bike, or boat, Laura hits all the hotspots in Amsterdam, such as the Rijksmuseum and the Hotel De L'Europe. She even takes a day-trip outside the city to explore neighboring Volendam and picturesque Volendam Harbor and drops into the Rembrandt Hoeve Cheesefarm and Clog Factory.

programme.title: Cambodia
programme.desc: Cambodia has recently risen as a must-see travel destination, and top-notch resorts and hotels have developed to accommodate travelers. Join Laura as she treks to the magnificent temples of Angkor Wat, Bayon, and Ta Prohm via one of Asia's most recognizable animals - the elephant.

programme.title: The Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Begin your stay along the Amalfi Coast in stunning Positano. They say Ravello is a town suspended between sea and sky, and it will leave an impression on you as it has on many artists, musicians, and writers. In Salerno, the gardens at Villa Rufolo will seer into your memory.

programme.title: Saigon
programme.desc: Saigon, Vietnam is an incredible place to visit. It has history, and cultural excursions, like cruising the Mekong Delta and visiting a floating marketplace. In Ho Chi Minh City you can shop until you drop, stay in five-star hotels, and enjoy an incredible culinary experience.

programme.title: Auckland
programme.desc: Auckland is New Zealand's largest city. Laura takes an hour's drive south of Auckland to a working sheep farm in the New Zealand countryside. A few miles down the road, Laura spies a familiar sight - Hobbiton, the set from the Lord of the Rings films where Bilbo lived before and after his journey.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Tahiti and Bora Bora
programme.desc: For sheer tropical splendor, the islands of Tahiti and Bora Bora stand alone. Hyper blue lagoons, white-sand beaches, fish of every shape, size, and color, as well as a generous and welcoming people make these islands key destinations for travelers from around the world.

Join ATG as we take a look at 6 terrible plot twists we saw coming from a mile away.

programme.title: Electric Fence; Mother and Child Reunion; Dog Saves Master; Life on a Line
programme.desc: A mother and her baby were miraculously saved after being thrown overboard in a raging storm, a mysterious force stops a man from touching a metal fence that had a hidden broken power line touching it, and a dog and his owner share a special connection as the dog saves the man's life. And more!

programme.title: Princess from the Sea
programme.desc: Moya, a tribal princess, flees her war-torn island. Two cultures unite as she helps the Robinsons build a new fortress. Ernest becomes infatuated with Moya, whose life is in danger from the dark spells of a shaman.

programme.title: Runaway Hearts
programme.desc: At a poignant moment in their lives, 11-year-old Tevin and his 5-year-old sister Angel escape their dysfunctional home to live in the streets. With nowhere to go, Tevin and Angel meet two people who need a miracle just as badly as they do.

programme.title: Frozen Stupid 2: Open Water
programme.desc: When Tony’s car is towed out of Lake Houghton (again), the D.N.R. decides to hit him with a huge fine. Luckily for Tony, there is a fishing tournament the upcoming weekend with a grand prize of $20,000, and he has the boat and lure to win.

programme.title: The Boy Who Loved Trolls
programme.desc: When 12-year-old Paul's wish that the wonderful stories he reads would come true is realized, he discovers a troll and a mermaid under a bridge. It turns out that the troll has less than a day to live, and Paul must choose to risk everything to save him.

programme.title: Bridge to Terabithia
programme.desc: When Leslie Burke moves in next door to Jess Aarons, Jess finds a friend in Leslie. Over time, they discover a secret place in the forest across a fallen pine tree, and over a creek, they call Terabithia, a place where memories are sacred.

programme.title: Necessary Parties
programme.desc: 14-year-old Chris Mills throws a wrench in his parents’ plans to divorce by hiring Archie Corelli, an auto-mechanic by day and a lawyer by night, to sue his parents and ultimately disrupt their plans to end their marriage.

programme.title: Gulliver's Travels
programme.desc: Giant Gulliver washes ashore on tiny Lilliput and attempts to prevent war between the small kingdom of Lilliput and its equally minuscule rival Blefuscu. In pursuit of his endeavor, can Gulliver smooth the way towards love between the Princess and Prince of the two opposing lands?

programme.title: On Our Own
programme.desc: Four newly orphaned siblings are out of options. With no blood relatives, they are about to be sent to separate foster homes. To keep from being split apart, they decide to bust out of the orphanage and take off in a beat-up VW in search of an estranged uncle, but detectives soon catch their tail.

programme.title: Lone Star Kid
programme.desc: After witnessing a severe accident, a compassionate 11-year-old boy named Brian Zimmerman believes that the town of Crabb, Texas needs a mayor, and Brian thinks he is "the man" for the job. This inspiring true story shows the potential for good that even a young boy can have on his community.

programme.title: Charlie & Me
programme.desc: This is the touching story of an 11-year-old girl who has an extraordinarily close relationship with her grandfather and a complex relationship with her widowed father. programme.title: The Wildman of Kentucky, The Mystery of Panther Rock
programme.desc: There is probably no other unknown creature that arouses more curiosity than the Bigfoot or Sasquatch. Yes, there is the Loch Ness Monster, the Chupacabra and other great beasts of Lore but the Bigfoot remains the most compelling as it pulls us towards ourselves…shadowing the unknown X factor of our very origins. The case files contain thousands of reported sightings, yet no actual specimen has ever been found. Hundreds of photographs exist, but the creature has not been identified. Still, the clues accumulate year after year. In the words of one Bigfoot investigator, “It is an extremely complex phenomenon with no starting point and few geographical limits.” If this creature does exist then it most certainly must be a relative of man. Species? Unknown at this time. In the heart of Kentucky there is an ancient and sacred ground known as Panther Rock. For many years tales of strange events have been reported but never investigated in full. Now, for the first time an intrepid group of explorers ventures into the unknown to discover the truth. Join the Reality Team of Special Investigators as they uncover new Bigfoot witnesses and historical tales. Journey with them into the dark woods of the Frazier Land and witness amazing paranormal and often terrifying events.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Alien Creatures from Beyond: Monsters, Ghosts and Vampires
programme.desc: Are there creatures still unknown to science lurking in the remote areas of our planet? Hundreds of eyewitnesses say unquestionably YES. Lurking in Magog is the elusive Memphre, a thirty-foot lake monster that stalks the peaceful waters of Lake Memphremagog. Wilno, Ontario is a small town steeped in its heritage, locals believe that when a person takes their own life, then is buried on sacred ground, that person will become a vampire who will walk the streets, preying on their family members. The Bytown Museum sits at the gateway to the Rideau Canal and may also be a gateway to the paranormal. Bell Island is a place steeped in mysteries and legends encountered firsthand by local residents living around the marshes known as Dobbin’s Garden. The residents have named their local Banshee “The Bell Island Hag” explaining that sometimes she appears as a beautiful woman in white, but more often as a horrifying deformed old hag. Men have been known to enter the marshes and then emerge days later scared to death with no memory of what happened, or where they had been. Banshees, Lake Monsters, Vampires and more will be encountered in this special compilation of “Alien Creatures from Beyond.”

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Beautiful Danger
programme.desc: Epic adventure awaits at the Dry Tortugas, but fishing off the grid is no easy task. As the SFTV crew discovers, preparation is everything.

programme.title: Young Salt, Old Spirit
programme.desc: Armed with the skills of generations past, rough and tumble New Englanders teach the SFTV crew how to catch the region's sporty summertime species.

programme.title: Before We Sink
programme.desc: The Brigade must contend with a crack in their voyageur canoe in preparation for an epic lake crossing and the most dangerous stretch of rapids. With time a constant pressure and the threat of failure looming, a storm threatens to freeze one of the brigade members. The team receives a surprise from home.

programme.title: Feral Sheep Hunting in Argentina
programme.desc: Jim heads the Argentina to go after some of the cool Barnyard sheep species.

programme.title: Number One Client
programme.desc: Despite his busy schedule, Tom never misses an opportunity to take Jacque on a hunt.

programme.title: Good Times and Good Bulls
programme.desc: Bowhunter's Mike Carney and friends chase bugling bull elk at Cross Mountain Ranch in northwestern Colorado.

programme.title: Texas Bone-Collecting
programme.desc: Stan Potts is headed to south Texas to collect bone at the Partidas Ranch with his buddy Michael Waddell, Dr. Deer shares the advantages of fire in mangement in your management plan, Mr. Shelton talks in-season archery practice and Jeremy Moore delivers part two of a three part series on shed dogs.

programme.title: Super Grouper
programme.desc: Chef Scott Leysath got a ton of grouper from his buddy, Tommy Gomes, and he’s cooking it up 3 different ways. Joining him on the show are Susie Jimenez, Stacy Lyn Harris, Brad Fenson, Cee Dub, and Buddy T.

programme.title: The Reluctant Bottom Feeder
programme.desc: Derek traverses Wisconsin for backbreaking labor on the Mississippi River, and a backbreaking fun at a hog wrestling tournament. Featuring Jeff Ritter.

programme.title: Naples Offshore Bonita Run
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Wes Bedell off the coast of Southwest Florida in the Gulf of Mexico. The search is on for schools of feisty bonita.

programme.title: Naples Largemouth Bass
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Gerry Brousseau for some fast largemouth bass action in Naples.

programme.title: Ground Zero
programme.desc: Bou and Rob work with Dr. Jerry Ault and his team from the University of Miami in an effort to place satellite tags on tarpon.

programme.title: Tarpon School
programme.desc: Catherine Fordyce attends the Florida Keys Fly Fishing School and tries to catch her first tarpon on fly with Rob.

programme.title: Quiet Cool
programme.desc: The backcountry and bluewater fishing grounds of Collier County, Florida, add to the area’s permanent vacation vibe.

programme.title: Get Me Off This Rock
programme.desc: Finding a secret fishing hideout in the Florida Keys is nearly impossible. Unless you know about Melody Key, Whidh porvides direct address to species ranging from snapper to shark.

programme.title: Deep Chaos
programme.desc: Swordfish are one of the fastest and most aggressive species on earth, and you won't find them any closer to the mainland as you will in Palm Beach, Florida.

programme.title: Guide For The Visiting Angler
programme.desc: Professional fishing guides Travis & Justin run through the do’s and don’ts and what to expect on a charter trip in Panama City Beach. Basically, how to have fun!

programme.title: Aimless Action
programme.desc: Travis comes back into town and Justin’s plan is to just “let it happen” and find success in the form of whatever hits their hook. Does it work?

programme.title: A Different Drum
programme.desc: Justin and his childhood friend run into a school of black drum, the elusive cousin of the much loved red drum (redfish), while out scouting and call the camera guy. Then Justin fulfills a childhood dream with actor John Schneider in the iconic “General Lee.”

programme.title: Windy Ways
programme.desc: No matter where you chase muskies, you will most likely encounter a period of big wind during the season. This often requires changing your game plan and fishing secondary spots, as well as making mental adjustments to make the most of your trip. Jim Saric and Trophy Hunter Tom Sullivan outline strategies for dealing with windy conditions to salvage your trip.

programme.title: Northwoods Knowledge
programme.desc: Casting artificial lures and trailing live bait is a tradition in the fall throughout the Wisconsin Northwoods. Yet everywhere across the musky range, fall conditions can be extreme as the musky season rapidly comes to an end. First, Jim Saric and Musky Hunters John Mich and Scott Kolpin fish dark water in unseasonably warm fall conditions. Then, Jim, Pro Guide Rob Manthei and John Mich tackle a clear water lake in blizzard conditions.

programme.title: Postpawn Smallies
programme.desc: Fishing for postspawn smallmouth bass. Subtle lures and swimming retrieves match the depth and mood of smallies on the move

programme.title: Eagle Lake Musky
programme.desc: Tackling giant muskies on Eagle Lake in northwest Ontario. How to cover water and convert follows into fish on the line

programme.title: Artificial Crappie
programme.desc: Fishing the deep weededges for summer crappies. Jigs and micro crankbaits target different depth ranges.

programme.title: Soldotna 1
programme.desc: This week we’re off to the golden fall colors of ptarmigan country. Larry Csonka shows why this hunt for a little bird is his favorite.

programme.title: Soldotna 2
programme.desc: Soldotna is an ideal place to start exploring the Kenai Peninsula. This week we’ll show you why Soldotna’s a great base of operations for your trip, and what you can expect to see on a visit.

programme.title: Canada 2
programme.desc: Nick Mundt, T-Bone Turner and Mason Waddell hunting Black Bears in Saskatchewan Canada (Part 2)

programme.title: Kimber 8400 Tactical
programme.desc: Kimber tactical rifles are built for real-world law enforcement and military use. Our experts take one to the range. Ruger fans will enjoy seeing the flat dark earth options from Davidson's. Taurus' Jessie Harrison shoots against an average Joe.

programme.title: The Owen
programme.desc: Joe Mantegna explores the unusual Australian submachine gun.

programme.title: Seth Feider - 1000 Islands
programme.desc: For the 2nd year in a row, ZAFS buddy, pro angler Seth Feider kicks off the season. Just like 2017, this one will be a Smallmouth bonanza. One difference, these fish are going to be remote, untouched remote. Welcome to Kong island.

programme.title: Presentation Tricks & Trends
programme.desc: The In-Fisherman staff reveals hard-won secrets from their extensive field research, as they rip spoons to put a grip on smallmouth bass, use rag-tag tactics for walleyes, and employ the newest softbait trailers for largemouth bass.

programme.title: Dolphin Backcountry Pro 18, Sheaffer 240V, Contender 44ST
programme.desc: Today, on Florida Sportsman Best Boat... for anglers looking to sightfish on the flats, we’ll be taking a look at the Dolphin 18 Back Country Pro; if you require a boat built forfishing along the mangroves and off the beaches, we’ll be looking at the Sheaffer S240; and...for the boater that wants speed, range and serious offshore fishing capability, we’ll be taking a look at Contender 44ST.

programme.title: 23’ Seacraft Back in Action, Billy Knowles Sea Trial
programme.desc: Wildfire Marine gets back to work on the 23a€TM Seacraft restoration; Two Rivers Boatworks puts in overtime to complete the 36 Yellowfin; George LaBonte joins dreamboat owner Steve Oatman aboard his dive-inspired 29a€TM World Cat; and...L&H rigs and sea trials the 36 Billy Knolwes project.

programme.title: Everglades Snook, Redfish & Bass with Capt. Benny Blanco and Capt. Albert Hernandez
programme.desc: America's Everglades are one of a kind. The seemingly endless exploration opportunities and world class fishing have captivated outdoorsman since they were first discovered. Capt. Benny Blanco and Capt. Albert Hernandez show the importance of protecting the Everglades for future generations.

programme.title: Alaska-Yukon Moose Archery Hunt
programme.desc: The Alaska-Yukon Moose hunt can be challenging, exhilarating and rewarding. This hunt is no exception. Greg is pushing his luck with a late-season foray into the snow-covered hills of the Yukon in search of adventure, a big bull and a great trophy. He sees a few great moose before coming across a bull he can't turn down. If you love moose, you'll love this hunt.

programme.title: Shankfest 5 Part 2
programme.desc: Shankfest 5 Group 2 arrives in camp to Choctaw Hunting Lodge with more hogs and rams on the menu.

programme.title: Best of Season 9
programme.desc: All the best hunts of Season 9 cut down to 30 minutes of nothing but arrows flingin and bullets flyin!

programme.title: Wild Wild West

programme.title: Our Dwellings Shape Us

programme.title: A Mayan Fowl Play
programme.desc: Chris Dorsey and good friend Francisco Bergaz travel into the thick jungles of the Yucatan Peninsula to hunt the gorgeous ocellated turkey.

programme.title: Airspeeder - Our Flying Car Future
programme.desc: “Nothing drives innovation like racing. The world is ready for advanced air mobility and we are proud to make history by introducing the world’s first racing series for flying electric cars. Airspeeder and EXA represent the future of motorsport and a compelling and exhilarating showcase of the potential of electric flying cars as this generation’s defining mobility revolution.” - Matthew Pearson, Founder, Airspeeder and Alauda Aeronautics - EXA is Airspeeder’s first electric flying racing series. Up to four teams with two remote pilots per team will compete in three individual events across the globe through 2021. They will race ‘blade-to-blade’ over locations inaccessible to traditional motorsport.

programme.title: Canoo Revealed
programme.desc: We are here to change the way the world thinks about transportation. Rather than designing our vehicles the traditional way, we design our vehicles from the inside out, crafting every feature with a focus on what matters most to our users to give them the best possible experience. programme.title: Electrified - The Current State of Electric Vehicles
programme.desc: Chelsea Sexton, Paul Scott, Forth Mobility, and several owners come together to discuss how electric cars have evolved and where we currently are in the state of this developing technology. It covers issues and experiences related to charging, battery degradation, and range anxiety, along with detailed explanations of charging levels, types of electric vehicles, and the future of hydrogen. - This film prepares viewers with the knowledge needed for properly assessing vehicle options, along with considerations for charging, and knowledge about what they may need to know before making a purchase.

programme.title: Who Stole the Electric Car?
programme.desc: In the year 1995, a self-centered average guy steals a prototype electric car in a crazy attempt to win back his Africa-bound environmentalist girlfriend. During his road trip from the Motor City to Southern California, he teams up with a vegetarian sidekick and, pursued by the police, the duo race across the country. . . without using a single drop of gasoline. - Directors: James Dastoli, Robert Dastoli - Starring: Carl Fieler, Chris Shields

programme.title: Astypalea: Smart, Sustainable Island
programme.desc: Astypalea up until now is probably only known to insiders. The small island is located in the Aegean Sea, it belongs to Greece and is especially known for its butterflies. This is likely to change in the future: Astypalea will become a model for smart, emission-free mobility. The island wants to prove that a purely electric transport system is already possible today – without any restrictions on the mobility of its inhabitants. We explain the details.

programme.title: The Porsche Taycan Goes Golfing

programme.title: The Porsche Press Conference at the L.A. Auto Show

programme.title: Audi Annual Press Conference 2020
programme.desc: 2020 was dominated by a global pandemic and great upheaval, which therefore shifted the focus even more strongly to the question of responsible actions. As part of the automotive industry, we are responsible for our employees and customers, for stable economic growth, and for a sustainable business model. Despite – or precisely because of – the current challenges, we are in a position where we can make a big difference. At Audi, we see ambitious climate targets, the paradigm shift toward software, and the impetus created by new competitors as an opportunity to play an active part in shaping the future of mobility. Our Board of Management team, which has been active in a new constellation for about a year, will provide an overview on how Audi handled the unusual year of 2020 and on which future topics we have our sights firmly set.

programme.title: Animation: Dynamic All-Wheel Steering – Maneuvering And Parking
programme.desc: An advance in all-wheel steering, the Dynamic All-wheel Steering that is optional in the Audi A6, A7, and A8, is standard equipment in the S8. It is currently the top technology among Audi’s steering systems and combines dynamic steering on the front axle with rear-axle steering. With that system, Audi is exploring the limits of what is physically possible. The system offers significant benefits, specifically in the threshold range. It combines direct, sporty steering response with masterful driving stability or, in brief: manageability with extremely high precision.

programme.title: Animation: Audi Q4 e-tron – Interior and package
programme.desc: With the Q4 e-tron, Audi is presenting a true all-rounder – it is a confident companion for everyday life and leisure, and is suitable in every way as a household’s main car. At 4,590 millimeters (15.1 ft) long, 1,865 millimeters (6.1 ft) wide, and 1,613 millimeters (5.3 ft) high, the exterior dimensions of the Q4 e-tron place it in the larger compact SUV segment. The architecture of the modular electric drive system (MEB) on which the compact electric SUV from Audi is based enables a completely new division of space. While the front overhang measures just 86 centimeters (33.9 in), the wheelbase measures a generous 2.76 meters (9.1 ft) – even more than in the medium-sized SUV segment. The resulting interior measures 1.83 meters (6.0 ft) in length, which is similar to a large full-size class SUV.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Interior Design and Seating Position
programme.desc: The fully electric gran turismo gives new impetus to the Audi design language: It is a dynamic sculpture that stands on the road as if sculpted from a full volume. The Audi e-tron GT proves: The packaging of an electric car with its large battery and the fascinating design of a gran turismo with a flat silhouette and powerful proportions are no contradiction. This is made possible by a recess in the battery pack. programme.title: Audi Annual Press Conference 2020
programme.desc: 2020 was dominated by a global pandemic and great upheaval, which therefore shifted the focus even more strongly to the question of responsible actions. As part of the automotive industry, we are responsible for our employees and customers, for stable economic growth, and for a sustainable business model. Despite – or precisely because of – the current challenges, we are in a position where we can make a big difference. At Audi, we see ambitious climate targets, the paradigm shift toward software, and the impetus created by new competitors as an opportunity to play an active part in shaping the future of mobility. Our Board of Management team, which has been active in a new constellation for about a year, will provide an overview on how Audi handled the unusual year of 2020 and on which future topics we have our sights firmly set.

programme.desc: UAE Warriors 9 brings to you live action from Mubadala Arena in Abu Dhabi on November 29th, 2019. Meanwhile in the middleweight division ONE Championship alumni Bakhtiyar Abbasov has been matched with Igor Litoshik and Ahmad Labban faces Magomedsultan Magomedsultanov.

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 1
programme.desc: They’re big. They’re bold. They’re fight stars. The best combat sport stars in the ring/cage, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including UFC sharp shooting Conor Mcgregor and the judo french force, Teddy Riner. We also look at fighters who have made it in Hollywood while learning the skilful art of trash talking from some of the best. Finally it’s the brightest duo in WWE, the Bella Twins!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 2
programme.desc: They’re big. They’re bold. They’re fight stars. The best combat sport stars in the ring, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including Britain's boxer Anthony Joshua while UFC’s Ronda Rousey has met her match. We also look at fighters who have made some nice coin and a footballer turned wrestler. Finally it’s a new star in the UFC, Paige VanZant!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 3
programme.desc: They’re bold. They’re fight stars. The best combat sport stars in the ring, cage and on the canvas, living it up outside of their sport, including the Filipino with a fighting spirit Manny Pacquiao and what the best in the UFC use to fuel their fights. We also look at the greatest, Muhammad Ali and the wrestler Helen Maroulis. Finally it’s the Hollywood superstar who hooked up with the wrestler!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 4
programme.desc: We Speak to “Rowdy” Ronda Rousey, and her old training partner, Kayla Harrison. We also look at some boxers who won an Olympic medal - before becoming a champion and Mexico’s finest, Canelo Alvarez. Finally, Nikki Bella found love with fellow wrestler, John Cena!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 5
programme.desc: China's biggest boxing star, Zou Shiming. In the UFC we step outside of the canvas to learn about colour commentator Joe - Rogan and some fighters who became politicians. Finally, it’s Kosovo’s first Olympic gold medallist and more of that trash talk!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 6
programme.desc: She is an inspiration across the globe and the next generation, also has dominated women's boxing, it's Nicola Adams. Join her fascinating journey of becoming one of the best British female boxers!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 7
programme.desc: They’re big. They’re bold. They’re fight stars. The best combat sport stars in the ring, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including some females dominating the fight world like Angela Lee and Paige VanZant. In the UFC we look at Michael Bisping’s clean slate win. - Finally, we can’t forget about Hollywood and Demi Lovato's love life while Sylvester Stallone learns how to box from the best!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 8
programme.desc: Wladimir Klitschko’s return to the ring and Hollywood’s Idris Elba entering the world of combat sports. In the UFC we look at Tito Ortiz and his love life. Finally, Irish boxer Katie Taylor and one of Hollywood’s biggest - stars, Jackie Chan!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 9
programme.desc: The rise and fall of Tyson Fury and Nicola Adams exciting start to the year. In the UFC we find out about the first man to beat Conor McGregor, Nate Diaz. Finally, it’s the heavyweight hero turned salesman, George Foreman and - Jay Z’s boxers in the ring!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 10
programme.desc: Floyd Mayweather Jr and his post boxing career and some anti trash talkers in the sport. In wrestling, we look at Japan’s big list of medallists at Rio 2016 and finally, it’s the boxer who went from fighting in the streets to the ring, - Robson Conceicao

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 11
programme.desc: The best combat sport stars in the cage and on the - canvas, living it up outside of their sport, including UFC veteran Anderson Silva, while 50 Cent tries to make it in the ring. Heavyweight boxer Anthony Joshua has a small surprise while there’s more women rising up the UFC ranks. And fight stars in films!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 12
programme.desc: UFC’s Jon Jones, Jay Z and Oscar De La Hoya hedge their bets. Carl Froch gets into some trash talk and we find out about more females setting their sights high in the combat world, from Cuban boxers to the American - boxer turned MMA fighter, Holly Holm!

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: S1 E24 | This week on Culture Q we dive into the world of Super Queer-oes, looking at DC's bisexual Superman and trans Wonder Woman character, as well as other upcoming projects like Marvel's The Eternals and Thor: Love and Thunder. Later we take a look at the Netflix employee walkout over Dave Chappelle's special The Closer, hearing from the employees affected as well as stars like Johnathan Van Ness and Our Lady J, before we sit down to interview Bowen Yang about his time on Saturday Night Live. Next, we congratulate Admiral Rachel Levine for becoming the first trans and the first female four-star officer in the US, and then go global looking at mounting tensions in Ghana, Russia, and Afghanistan. Finally we celebrate Jamie Lee Curtis's daughter Ruby coming out as trans, and look at Curtis's history with the Human Rights Campaign, and her upcoming biopic based on the woman who founded the Free Mom Hugs organization.

programme.title: Putting On

Behind the scenes at a swimwear shoot with trans models, Leith Ashley and Atticus Rank. 2 out Polo champions discuss their involvement with the Gay Polo League.

programme.title: My Trans Life
programme.desc: Being trans is a mental, physical and emotional journey and MY TRANS LIFE showcases inspiring trans individuals on their journeys of acceptance. From preparing for major surgery, to tackling love lives, to campaigning for equality, MY TRANS LIFE follows transgender people facing the world in the body they were meant to be in.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Rave Train
programme.desc: Rave Train is a video series that features live EDM DJ and Artist performances with a diverse range of dancers from the Rave culture. SOUL TRAIN meets EDM; Rave Train brings movement to sound with the latest dance styles with today’s upcoming Electronic Music artists.

programme.desc: As the AIDS epidemic in New York escalated during the '80s, a young, out, black producer creates a series of public television programs focused on HIV/AIDS, bringing folks who were previously ignored by mainstream media to the core of the public discussion.

programme.title: Jobriath A.D.
programme.desc: Known as the first openly gay rock star, Jobriath’s reign was a brief two years. Done in by over-hyped publicity, shunned by the gay community, and dismissed by critics, Jobriath retreated to the Chelsea Hotel, where he died forgotten, one of the earliest casualties of AIDS. But years later, new fans discover his music, and acts such as The Pet Shop Boys, Def Leppard, and Morrissey cite him as an influence. Experience the heartbreaking, unbelievable story of the one, the only, Jobriath.

programme.title: The Drag Roast Of Heklina
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Check your political correctness at the door and bring your finest, biggest wig for a raucous, no-holds-barred roast of one of San Francisco’s favorite larger-than-life drag personalities, the one and only Heklina—aka Stefan Grygelko. This Revry Original special features such roasters as Jackie Beat, Julie Brown (Clueless), Peaches Christ, Sister Roma, Alaska Thunderf*ck, and Jinkx Monsoon.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Coming of Age in Cherry Grove
programme.desc: Founded in 1869, Cherry Grove (Fire Island, NY) is considered by most to be the first openly LGBTQ community in the United States. It has become known as one of the most accepting resort communities in the world – a place where you can not only discover who you are, but also freely experiment with who or what (gender) you may want to become. Cherry Grove is also known for the famous “INVASION” – an annual ritual that takes place every July 4th as a celebration of gender acceptance. This film tells the stories of a variety of long-term residents and what they find so wonderful about life in Cherry Grove.

programme.title: Vox Luminis: Handel in Versailles
programme.desc: È nella sontuosa Cappella Reale di Versailles che il gruppo Vox Luminis porta Georg Friedrich Handel sotto i riflettori. Specializzato nel repertorio barocco inglese, italiano e tedesco, il gruppo Vox Luminis, sotto la direzione di Lionel Meunier, esegue con leggerezza e raffinatezza due salmi, un'opera lirica e un oratorio.

programme.title: Vasily Petrenko: Dvořák - Beethoven
programme.desc: Una chiamata dal destino? Messaggi rivoluzionari segreti nascosti nella musica? La Quinta Sinfonia di Beethoven è una delle opere più esaminate nella storia della musica. Comunque la si interpreti, è senza dubbio una delle composizioni più potenti e magistrali mai scritte. Ascoltate questa sinfonia drammatica e commovente eseguita dalla Israel Philharmonic Orchestra sotto la raffinata direzione di Vasily Petrenko.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker - S. Rattle
programme.desc: L'illustre Orchestra Filarmonica di Berlino, la Berliner Philharmoniker, ha fatto dell'Europakonzert una tradizione. Ogni anno i suoi musicisti celebrano la fondazione della loro orchestra in una città europea diversa. Nel 2008 si sono esibiti sotto alla direzione del grande direttore d'orchestra Sir Simon Rattle al Conservatorio Tchaikovsky di Mosca. In programma: Il Concerto per violino n. 1 in SOL minore di Max Bruch, la Sinfonia n. 7 di Beethoven e la Sinfonia di Igor Stravinsky in tre movimenti.

programme.title: Verbier Festival: Evgeny Kissin
programme.desc: Autentica star del pianoforte, il musicista russo Evgeny Kissin è ospite fisso del Verbier Festival in Svizzera, dove si è esibito più volte dalla prima edizione del 1994. La Sonata per pianoforte n. 59 di Haydn, la Sonata per pianoforte n. 32 di Beethoven e la "Melodia" di Christoph Willibald Gluck da Orfeo ed Euridice offrono a Kissin l'opportunità di mostrare la portata del suo virtuosismo e il lirismo delle sue interpretazioni, ma anche il suo carisma fenomenale.

programme.title: Symphonic Dances: Zahia Ziouani
programme.desc: A capo dell' Orchestra Sinfonica Divertimento (fondata nel 1998, in residenza a Stains dal 2005), Zahia Ziouani è riuscita a diversificare il pubblico della musica classica. Gli studenti dei conservatori della regione dell'Île-de-France si uniscono a lei per un viaggio nel repertorio sinfonico sotto il segno della danza, dalla tarantella italiana alla farandola provenzale, passando per il gopak ucraino.

programme.title: Giuseppe Verdi: La Traviata - ORW
programme.desc: La Traviata, "La Devota", un'opera in tre atti, con un libretto di Francesco Maria Piave basato sul romanzo e la commedia La Dame aux Camélias di Alexandre Dumas fils, è una delle opere più popolari. Rappresenta la redenzione attraverso l'amore per mezzo del personaggio di Violetta. Questo ruolo, notevolmente interpretato da Patrizia Ciofi che unisce forza e fragilità, richiede assoluto virtuosismo.

programme.title: Lang Lang - Piano Recital
programme.desc: La scelta di Lang Lang per la musica e la modalità di presentazione ha affermato la sua sensibilità del XXI° secolo rendendo al tempo stesso omaggio ai suoi precedenti pianistici e ai suoi mentori. Non è stato certo un caso che abbia suonato Wanderer Fantasy di Schubert, la prima opera che il suo insegnante del Curtis Institute, Gary Graffman, aveva registrato e usato per concludere il concerto delle Réminiscences Du Don Juan de Mozart di Liszt, associato ai più grandi virtuosi del pianoforte.

programme.desc: Le eroine del compositore Giacomo Puccini erano quasi sempre condannate a un tragico destino. Qui vengono portate sul palco accompagnate dalle arie più belle. Questa coreografia è un omaggio all'opera, e in particolare all'illustre compositore scomparso.

Qui dirige il Collegium Vocal de Gand, che ha fondato nel 1970. A Parigi, nella chiesa barocca di Saint-Roch, le sontuose voci di Grace Davidson (soprano), Damien Guillon (controtenore), Thomas Hobbs (tenore) e Peter Kooij (basso) risuonano in un programma religioso dedicato al Natale.

Una serata dedicata al compositore tedesco nel centocinquantesimo anniversario della sua morte, con la sua Sinfonia n. 4 in re minore.

programme.desc: Il Festival "Les Coups de Cœur à Chantilly" concede a Renaud Capuçon ucarta bianca come solista e direttore musicale dei Solisti dell'Accademia Menuhin. Questa accademia, fondata in Svizzera dal famoso violinista Yehudi Menuhin (1916-1999), accoglie dal 1977 i migliori strumentisti ad arco e li riunisce per concerti in tutto il mondo.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker - S. Rattle
programme.desc: L'illustre Orchestra Filarmonica di Berlino, la Berliner Philharmoniker, ha fatto dell'Europakonzert una tradizione. Ogni anno i suoi musicisti celebrano la fondazione della loro orchestra in una città europea diversa. Nel 2008 si sono esibiti sotto alla direzione del grande direttore d'orchestra Sir Simon Rattle al Conservatorio Tchaikovsky di Mosca. In programma: Il Concerto per violino n. 1 in SOL minore di Max Bruch, la Sinfonia n. 7 di Beethoven e la Sinfonia di Igor Stravinsky in tre movimenti.

programme.title: Beethoven: Ode to Joy
programme.desc: In occasione del 20° anniversario dello Young Euro Classic - un festival che riunisce giovani musicisti promettenti provenienti dai 28 paesi dell'Unione europea - la European Union Youth Orchestra esegue una nuova versione della Sinfonia n. 9 op. 125 di Ludwig van Beethoven. L'ultimo tempo di questa sinfonia, composta nel 1823, è un vero successo della musica classica. È il preludio dell'Inno alla gioia, che dal 1970 è divenuto l'inno europeo suonato in occasione delle nelle cerimonie ufficiali.

I Gioielli di George Balanchine sono parte integrante del repertorio della compagnia - uno dei più grandi al mondo, sia per numero che per fama.

(Ri)scoprite lo splendore dell'età d'oro del barocco francese con questo programma esclusivo su Qwest TV.

programme.title: Daniel Barenboim - W. E. Orchestra
programme.desc: Orchestra di portata molto simbolica, la West-Eastern Divan Orchestra è stata creata grazie allo slancio del direttore israelo-argentino Daniel Barenboim e del critico letterario Edward Saïd. Riunisce tutti i giovani musicisti israeliani e dei paesi arabi vicini - come ad esempio la Siria, la Giordania o i territori palestinesi - con un unico obiettivo: gettare dei ponti fra le comunità attraverso la musica. In diretta dalla Philharmonie di Berlino nel 2006, interpretano l’imponente nona sinfonia di Beethoven.
